#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:1
msgid "_style_context"
msgstr "_style_context"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:3
msgid "Firma"
msgstr "Signature"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:9
msgid "Che problema risolve"
msgstr "What problem it solves"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:11
msgid ""
"Applica uno stile Matplotlib temporaneo e rende coerente il comportamento"
" delle figure create da `mespy`, soprattutto nei notebook "
"IPython/Jupyter."
msgstr "Applies a temporary Matplotlib style and keeps the behaviour of figures created by `mespy` consistent, especially in IPython/Jupyter notebooks."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:13
msgid "Contratto sugli input"
msgstr "Input contract"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:15
msgid ""
"`style=None` non aggiunge uno stile extra e lascia validi gli `rcParams` "
"correnti."
msgstr "`style=None` does not add any extra style and leaves the current `rcParams` in effect."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:16
msgid "`style=\"mespy\"` carica il file di stile incluso nel package."
msgstr "`style=\"mespy\"` loads the style file bundled with the package."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:17
msgid "Qualunque altra stringa viene passata a Matplotlib come nome stile."
msgstr "Any other string is passed to Matplotlib as a style name."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:19
msgid "Dove viene usata"
msgstr "Where it is used"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:21
msgid "in [`histogram`](../../moduli/plot_utils/histogram.md)"
msgstr "in [`histogram`](../../moduli/plot_utils/histogram.md)"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:22
msgid "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md)"
msgstr "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md)"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:24
msgid "Come fallisce"
msgstr "How it fails"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:26
msgid ""
"Se Matplotlib non riesce a caricare lo stile richiesto, propaga l'errore "
"del backend di stile sottostante."
msgstr "If Matplotlib cannot load the requested style, it propagates the error raised by the underlying style backend."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:27
msgid ""
"In ambiente notebook, alla fine del blocco mostra le nuove figure create "
"e poi le chiude per evitare il doppio display automatico."
msgstr "In notebook environments, at the end of the block it shows the new figures that were created and then closes them to avoid double automatic display."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:29
msgid "Perche resta privata"
msgstr "Why it remains private"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/style-context.md:31
msgid ""
"E un dettaglio infrastrutturale condiviso dalle funzioni di plotting. "
"Documentarlo chiarisce il comportamento del package, ma non e pensato "
"come interfaccia pubblica stabile."
msgstr "It is an infrastructural detail shared by the plotting functions. Documenting it clarifies the package behaviour, but it is not intended as a stable public interface."

